"{\"uid\": \"thevermilion.com-bishops-and-cardinals-against-macrons-olympics-article_5098\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This week the whole world has been commenting on the drag queens' performance at the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The reference to the Last Supper of Jesus with the \\u2026  Written by: Jack Williams  Published on:August 5, 2024  This week the whole world has been commenting on the drag queens' performance at the opening ceremony of theParis 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The reference to the Last Supper of Jesus with the apostles was evident and the protagonist Barbara Butch herself had claimed this comparison on her Instagram profile.\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.625099664836125e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faced with controversy and protests, director Thomas Jolly was forced to apologize, claiming however that he was inspired by Dionysus.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9992087045747664, \"rank\": 0.0005877495335575217, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7203611749372536e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Words that did not convince the Christians (and not only) who remainedscandalizedfor the provocation.\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 714, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9965277844581576, \"rank\": 0.002305391631756524, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scenes of the ceremony on Friday, July 26 also provoked a harsh reaction from an important part of the world's Catholic episcopate.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4896883875574403e-17, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The performance did not please the bishops of the house who released a statement in which they spoke of\\\"scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity, whichwe deploredeeply\\\".The episcopate of the Alps wanted to thank\\\"the representatives of other religious faiths who have expressed their solidarity with us\\\".In the uncomfortable position of bishops of the country promoting the controversial ceremony, the transalpine prelates have addressed a thought \\\"to all Christians on all continents who have been hurt by the excess and provocation of certain scenes.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9998704231841481, \"rank\": 0.0001295933701605953, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1382, \"end\": 1392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9965277844581576, \"rank\": 0.002305391631756524, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We want them to understand that the Olympic celebration is rightbeyond prejudicesideological of some artists\\\".\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the first to react to the images of the ceremony was MonsignorCharles SciclunaMetropolitan Archbishop of Malta and Adjunct Secretary of the Dicastery for the Doctrine of the Faith, who wrote a message to the French ambassador on the Mediterranean island to express his\\\"suffering and great disappointment at the insult made to us Christians during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1688, \"end\": 1698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9999896860085596, \"rank\": 9.678304388959275e-06, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999997521627, \"rank\": 2.477799411973769e-10, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}, {\"begin\": 1805, \"end\": 1811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999282579180435, \"rank\": 6.0691664564308605e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1926, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9965277844581576, \"rank\": 0.002305391631756524, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Scicluna, who is also president of the Maltese Bishops' Conference, invited his followers to do the same in a message on X.\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.6289733459301738, \"rank\": 0.5400250582727605, \"text\": \"Maltese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another bishop among the first to react was MonsignorRobert Barronhead of the Diocese of Winona-Rochester and an expert communicator, who condemned the scene in a video, wondering whether the organizers\\\"would they ever have daredmake fun of Islamin a similar way?\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2211, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"score\": 0.9892654137746267, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Winona-Rochester\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"and adding that\\\"this deeply secularist and postmodern society knows who its enemy is - they are naming him - and we should believe them.\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Barron also said that\\\"we should resist, we should make our voices heard.\\\"\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.2351298079476496e-13, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In these hours, a group of bishops including three cardinals have decided to sign a letter of protest for the opening ceremony and to address it to theInternational Olympic CommitteeThe letter reads:\\\"The world has watched with shock as the Paris Summer Olympics opened with a grotesque and blasphemous representation of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is difficult to understand how the faith of over 2 billion people can be socasually and intentionally blasphemous\\\".Therefore, none of the 27 bishops who signed believed the director's backtracking, who claimed not to have been inspired by the Last Supper.We, Catholic bishops of the world, on behalf of Christians throughout the world, ask the Olympic Committee to repudiate this blasphemous act and to apologize to all people of faith,\\\"is stated in the letter.\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 3399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3197, \"end\": 3205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4896883875574403e-17, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9965277844581576, \"rank\": 0.002305391631756524, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the signatories are three cardinals: the AmericanRaymond Leo Burkethe South AfricanWilfrid Fox Napierand the EthiopianBerhaneyesus Demerew Souraphiel.\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3497, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\", \"score\": 0.9981876916634764, \"rank\": 0.0017407381243292074, \"text\": \"Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to them, 24 other bishops and archbishops, mostly Americans, have signed.\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3642, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them is Monsignor Salvatore Joseph Cordileone, Metropolitan Archbishop of San Francisco.\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3657, \"end\": 3666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monsignor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0367500358629876e-20, \"text\": \"Monsignor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monsignor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monsignor\"}, {\"begin\": 3667, \"end\": 3694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvatore_Cordileone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salvatore Joseph Cordileone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvatore_Cordileone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salvatore_Cordileone\"}, {\"begin\": 3723, \"end\": 3736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"score\": 0.9999946965358166, \"rank\": 5.30349178997872e-06, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a week of silence, the Holy See tootook a standpublic on the representation of the opening ceremony of Paris 2024.The Press Office issued a note yesterday afternoon in French in which it states that\\\"The Holy See was saddened by some scenes of the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games in Paris and cannot but join the voices that have been raised in recent days to deplore the offence inflicted on so many Christians and believers ofother religions\\\".\", \"from\": 3741, \"to\": 4197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3850, \"end\": 3860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.578812289573765e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3915, \"end\": 3921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999282579180435, \"rank\": 6.0691664564308605e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4035, \"end\": 4040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999966948963, \"rank\": 3.304956626907205e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4153, \"end\": 4163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9965277844581576, \"rank\": 0.002305391631756524, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement also addresses the issue of freedom of expression and says:\\\"At a prestigious event where the whole world gathers around common values, there should be no allusions that ridicule the religious beliefs of many people.\", \"from\": 4199, \"to\": 4428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Freedom of expression, which, of course,it is not questionedfinds its limit in respecting others\\\"  Jack Williams  Jack Williams established himself as the editor-in-chief of The Vermilion with rigorous journalistic traits and an incessant quest for truth.\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4528, \"end\": 4532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9999846968978507, \"rank\": 8.585513387653398e-06, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 4543, \"end\": 4547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9999846968978507, \"rank\": 8.585513387653398e-06, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His career began as an investigative reporter, where he quickly gained a reputation for his in-depth research and insightful articles.\", \"from\": 4685, \"to\": 4819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams takes his role at The Vermilion very seriously.\", \"from\": 4823, \"to\": 4879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since he became editor-in-chief, he has set an editorial line based on impartiality, factual accuracy, and context relevance; this has established The Vermilion as a reference for political, economic, and global news.\", \"from\": 4880, \"to\": 5097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5031, \"end\": 5040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermilion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.282122590579433e-17, \"text\": \"Vermilion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermilion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermilion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": 